<br>
As for the others, both the tainted lightbringers and the damned soft Tier'dal who walk with our enemies, we can only act upon what we feel.  If they come before you and are found wanting... cut them down.  If He desires their service, He will return them in some way.<br>
<br>
What are you doing wrong?  I can not answer that.  I can only tell you my observations based on your notes.  You doubt yourself, it seems, because the rewards you wish are not  forthcoming.  We do not always receive the reward we deserve, when we feel we deserve it.  All things come in time, for some it takes longer then others.  Obstacles merely prove dedication, and make us stronger.  I will not sift the blame and say something trite as &quot;His Will bring all things at the time HE wishes,&quot; because it is simply not true.  We make our own path.  There are many diffrent roads to his Will.<br>
<br>
Do as you say you always have done.  Tear through whatever stands between you and where you wish to be.  Rend it asunder with your sword.  Burn it with your touch.  The very fact these things attempt to prevent you from your goals should be reason enough to destroy them.<br>
<br>
Through destruction we will grow, that is the way it has always been.<br>
<br>
<br>
~Vabris Vy'Tok, of House Vy'Tok<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk, Acolyte of Saryrn<br>
((edited for spelling))<br>
