<br>
The pure will not aid, assist, or touch those of the light save with an instrument of death. They will not allow a paladin to lay hands on them, even should it cause them to fall. This is a valid path. <br>
<br>
The corrupter's path is no less valid. They will use the ones of light, but consistently, and only so that they may be turned to darkness.  Would it not be right, for a cleric of Innoruuk, such as Gray, to try and spread the faith of his evil god to others? And to do such would he not have to walk among the &quot;unbelievers&quot;?<br>
<br>
Those of the light of course, have it much less hard. For sometimes good may see a hint of hope for one of darkness, and their gods are more of mercy and kindness.<br>
<br>
I of course, am a despised neutral. I do not mutter of the balance, but rather enjoy my ale, and sing songs where they will hear me, and leave the agonizing on the gods to such as you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
