<br>
The gods of Norrath do not use us as tools, but as agents of their agendas.  As I serve the Plaguelord, Bertoxxulous, and have served him always, I am an agent of his Scourge upon Norrath.  Although I may bind the wounds of my companions, it is still in greater service to the Scourge that I do so. Those who serve other gods, I am sure, will spread the will of their god, until the god of change, the god of death, grants them the chance to change their nature, to change who they serve.  Those who do not accept this change, act as agents of the darker aspects of their gods.  A northland shaman, twisted by corruption, will still be an agent of Justice, but of it's darker aspects.  A child of the Healer fallen can do the blackest acts in the name of that unspeakable one, as many of those with an eye missing can attest to.  Even Love and Honor have their darker aspects, and can be twisted to zealotry.  I need not relate the cruelty possible from a Mother, even the Mother of All, upon her children.<br>
<br>
Those who claim to have forsaken their gods, or to have been forsaken, read my words carefully.  The Gods do not let their agents leave their will undone.  They only allow their will to be placed upon Norrath, and those who fall allow their god to advance their darker agendas.<br>
<br>
Timogen, Warrior of the Scourge <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23>Hero Heart Tavern</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

